), and the combined characters of the terminalia (
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FF736E60E760FBA7" box="[159,303,1045,1071]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 30–36" captionStart-1="FIGURES 37–40" captionStartId-0="12.[150,271,1898,1922]" captionStartId-1="13.[151,274,1477,1501]" captionTargetBox-0="[154,1435,203,1857]" captionTargetBox-1="[162,1433,207,1417]" captionTargetId-0="figure-61@12.[150,1436,194,1877]" captionTargetId-1="figure-234@13.[151,1436,194,1456]" captionTargetPageId-0="12" captionTargetPageId-1="13" captionText-0="FIGURES 30–36. Longibeccus fuscovittatus (Ricardo), male wing and terminalia. 30. Right wing; 31–33. Lateral, dorsal and ventral views; 34. Gonostylus; 35–36. Aedeagus, dorsal and lateral views. Abbr.: r4, m3=cells; cerc=cercus; epand=epandrium; epiph= epiphallus; goncx=gonocoxite; hypd=hypandrium; pvapod=posteroventral aedeagal apodeme." captionText-1="FIGURES 37–40. Longibeccus fuscovittatus (Ricardo), female terminalia. 37–38. Dorsal and ventral views; 39. Spermathecae; 40. Genital fork. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; tg8, tg9=tergite 8, tergite 9; st8=sternite 8." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs. 31–40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FED06E60E7C5FBA7" box="[316,394,1045,1071]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 41–47" captionStart-1="FIGURES 48–51" captionStartId-0="18.[150,268,1749,1773]" captionStartId-1="19.[151,276,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1431,198,1719]" captionTargetBox-1="[159,1428,693,1895]" captionTargetId-0="figure-196@18.[151,1436,197,1729]" captionTargetId-1="figure-293@19.[151,1436,665,1905]" captionTargetPageId-0="18" captionTargetPageId-1="19" captionText-0="FIGURES 41–47. Longibeccus imperator (Oldroyd), male, wing and terminalia. 41. Left wing. Figures 42–44. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral views; 45. Gonostylus; 46–47. Aedeagus, dorsal and lateral views. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; distph=disti phallus; epand=epandrium; ep iph=epiphallus; goncx=gon ocoxit e; hypd=hyp andrium; pvapod=posteroventral apodeme." captionText-1="FIGURES 48–51. Longibeccus imperator (Oldroyd), female terminalia. 48–49. Dorsal and ventral views; 50. Spermathecae; 51. Genital fork. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; tg8= tergite 8, tg9=tergite 9; st7=sternite 7, st8=sternite 8." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">42–51</figureCitation>
). The large plate-like epiphallus concealing the distiphallus dorsally is diagnostic of the genus (35, 36, 46, 47). The epiphallus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D6DFF97FFE1FD686E4EE55CFBDC" authorityName="Scarbrough" authorityYear="2005" box="[644,787,1083,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Afroestricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951EAFCFF97FFE1FD686E4EE55CFBDC" box="[644,787,1083,1108]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Afroestricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FCC86E4EE534FBDD" box="[804,891,1083,1109]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,297,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[151,1436,269,1897]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Afroestricus flavipes (Loew), male terminalia (reillustrated after Scarbrough 2005). 13–15. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral views; 16. Aedeagus, lateral view; 17a–c. Spermathecae, A. flavipes; 18. Type labels, A. flavipes. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; distph=distiphallus; epand=epandrium; epiph= epiphallus; goncx=gonocoxite; hypd=hypandrium; pvapod=posteroventral aedeagal apodeme." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D6DFF97FFE1FC7F6E4EE27CFBDC" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1958" box="[915,1075,1083,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Cophinopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951EAFCFF97FFE1FC7F6E4EE27CFBDC" box="[915,1075,1083,1108]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Cophinopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FBA86E4EE2D3FBDD" box="[1092,1180,1083,1109]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1653,1677]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,205,1624]" captionTargetId="figure-139@9.[161,1426,194,1632]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Cophinopoda pulchripes Bigot, male terminalia. 19. Epandrium; 20. Gonocoxite and hypandrium; 21. Aedeagus; 22. Female, sternite 8; 23. Spermathecae. Abbr.: distph=distiphallus; epiph=epiphallus; goncx=gonocoxite; pvapod=posteroventral aedeagal apodeme; spmth caps= spermathecal capsule." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D6DFF97FFE1FB5F6E4EE314FBDC" authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1866" box="[1203,1371,1083,1108]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Emphysomera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951EAFCFF97FFE1FB5F6E4EE314FBDC" box="[1203,1371,1083,1108]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Emphysomera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FA806E4EE6F9FBF2" captionStart="FIGURES 24–29" captionStartId="10.[151,271,1811,1835]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,389,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-129@10.[151,1436,381,1790]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 24–29. Emphysomera atrogaster Bigot (reillustrated after Scarbrough &amp; Marascia 1996). 24. Right wing. 25–26. Lateral and dorsal views, terminalia; 27. Aedeagus, lateral view; 28.Male abdomen; 29. Spermathecae. Abbr.; epand=epandrium, epiph=epiphallus, distph=distiphallus, hypd=hypandrium, goncxp=gonocoxital process, r =4th radial 4 cell; pvapod=posteroventral aedeagal apodeme." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D6DFF97FFE1FF166E14E725FBF2" authorityName="Oldroyd" authorityYear="1970" box="[250,362,1121,1146]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Thallosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951EAFCFF97FFE1FF166E14E725FBF2" box="[250,362,1121,1146]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Thallosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FE976E15E7ADFBF2" box="[379,482,1120,1146]" captionStart="FIGURES 102–105" captionStartId="39.[151,270,1878,1902]" captionTargetBox="[155,1430,195,1827]" captionTargetId="figure-52@39.[150,1436,194,1857]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 102–105. Thallosia congiola Oldroyd (reillustrated from Tsacas &amp; Artigas 1994). 102. Epandrium, lateral; 103. Gonocoxite and hypandrium, lateral; 104. Aedeagus, lateral; 105. Female terminalia, ventral view. Abbr.: distph=distiphallus; epiph=epiphallus; goncx=gonocoxite; hypd=hypandrium; pvapod=posteroventral aedeagal apodeme; tg8=tergite 8." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 104</figureCitation>
) is also dorsal prominent but otherwise structurally different. The cercus which extends onto the ventral surface of the ventral lamella and the oval spermathecal bulbs are distinctive of females (
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FEEA6EDEE724FB4D" box="[262,363,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–40" captionStartId="13.[151,274,1477,1501]" captionTargetBox="[162,1433,207,1417]" captionTargetId="figure-234@13.[151,1436,194,1456]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 37–40. Longibeccus fuscovittatus (Ricardo), female terminalia. 37–38. Dorsal and ventral views; 39. Spermathecae; 40. Genital fork. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; tg8, tg9=tergite 8, tergite 9; st8=sternite 8." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs. 39</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FE956EDEE7D4FB4D" box="[377,411,1195,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–51" captionStartId="19.[151,276,1926,1950]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,693,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-293@19.[151,1436,665,1905]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 48–51. Longibeccus imperator (Oldroyd), female terminalia. 48–49. Dorsal and ventral views; 50. Spermathecae; 51. Genital fork. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; tg8= tergite 8, tg9=tergite 9; st7=sternite 7, st8=sternite 8." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">50</figureCitation>
). In other genera, the cercus covers only the dorsal surface of the pygidium, and the spermathecal bulbs are usually 3 or more times longer than wide and recurved (
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FBBE6EA5E2F9FB62" box="[1106,1206,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–18" captionStartId="7.[151,270,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,297,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-89@7.[151,1436,269,1897]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13–18. Afroestricus flavipes (Loew), male terminalia (reillustrated after Scarbrough 2005). 13–15. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral views; 16. Aedeagus, lateral view; 17a–c. Spermathecae, A. flavipes; 18. Type labels, A. flavipes. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; distph=distiphallus; epand=epandrium; epiph= epiphallus; goncx=gonocoxite; hypd=hypandrium; pvapod=posteroventral aedeagal apodeme." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Figs. 17</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FB286EA5E2ABFB62" box="[1220,1252,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1653,1677]" captionTargetBox="[164,1424,205,1624]" captionTargetId="figure-139@9.[161,1426,194,1632]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Cophinopoda pulchripes Bigot, male terminalia. 19. Epandrium; 20. Gonocoxite and hypandrium; 21. Aedeagus; 22. Female, sternite 8; 23. Spermathecae. Abbr.: distph=distiphallus; epiph=epiphallus; goncx=gonocoxite; pvapod=posteroventral aedeagal apodeme; spmth caps= spermathecal capsule." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">23</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FB1D6EA5E35EFB62" box="[1265,1297,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 64–66" captionStartId="28.[150,269,1612,1636]" captionTargetBox="[190,1406,180,1598]" captionTargetId="figure-168@28.[183,1412,170,1608]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 64–66. Ommatius coperitus n. sp., female terminalia. 64. Ventral view; 65. Genital fork; 66. Spermathecae, posterior view. Abbr.: cerc=cercus; st8=sternite 8; vl=ventral lamella; spmth=spermatheca; spmth duct=spermatheca with coiled duct; spmth vlv=spermathecal valve." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">66</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FAF36EA5E370FB62" box="[1311,1343,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 79–82" captionStartId="31.[151,277,1974,1998]" captionTargetBox="[204,1392,446,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-132@31.[191,1402,433,1972]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 79–82. Ommatius neotenellus Bromley, female terminalia. 79–80. Dorsal and ventral views; 81. Spermathecae; 82. Genital fork." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">81</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FAA06EA5E321FB62" box="[1356,1390,1232,1258]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–98" captionStartId="36.[151,269,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[210,1392,448,1946]" captionTargetId="figure-142@36.[192,1407,430,1990]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURES 95–98. Ommatius ultimus n. sp., female terminalia. 95–96. Dorsal and ventral views; 97. Spermathecae; 98. Genital fork." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">97</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D6DFF97FFE1FF7B6E83E76AFA87" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1839" box="[151,293,1270,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Michotamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951EAFCFF97FFE1FF7B6E83E76AFA87" box="[151,293,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Michotamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the spermathecal duct is looped or tightly coiled (
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FC9B6E83E581FA98" box="[887,974,1270,1296]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–57" captionStartId="22.[151,274,1863,1887]" captionTargetBox="[190,1395,266,1833]" captionTargetId="figure-94@22.[186,1401,239,1871]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 52–57. Michotamia coarctata Macquart, female. 52. Right wing; 53. Sternite 8 with genital apodeme (sternite 10?); 54. Genital furca; 55. Spermatheca with coiled duct; 56. Michotamia aurata (Fabricius 1794) (Oriental species; Scarrough &amp; Hill 2000), male terminalia, lateral view; 57. Aedeagus, lateral view. Abbr.: genapod=genital apodeme; flgm=flagellum; spmth=spermatheca; spmth duct=spermatheca with coiled duct; spmth vlv=spermathecal valve; st8=sternite 8; tg8=tergite 8." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9A36EEFF97FFE1FF296F6EE4B9FAD2" blockId="11.[151,1436,330,1370]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName id="4C254D6DFF97FFE1FF296F6EE715FABC" authorityName="Scarbrough" authorityYear="2010" box="[197,346,1307,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Longibeccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B951EAFCFF97FFE1FF296F6EE715FABC" box="[197,346,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Longibeccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confined to the African Continent with 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D6DFF97FFE1FCBF6F6EE247FABC" authorityName="Ricardo" authorityYear="1900" box="[851,1032,1307,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscovittatus">
<emphasis id="B951EAFCFF97FFE1FCBF6F6EE247FABC" box="[851,1032,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">L. fuscovittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
widespread whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D6DFF97FFE1FAEA6F6EE3D3FABC" authorityName="Oldroyd" authorityYear="1936" box="[1286,1436,1307,1332]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Longibeccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imperator">
<emphasis id="B951EAFCFF97FFE1FAEA6F6EE3D3FABC" box="[1286,1436,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">L. imperator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are only recorded from equatorial Africa (
<figureCitation id="131E2A6BFF97FFE1FD6E6F35E4A6FAD2" box="[642,745,1344,1370]" captionStart="FIGURE 108" captionStartId="42.[151,255,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,461,1746]" captionTargetId="figure-217@42.[150,1436,455,1750]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 108. Distribution of Longibeccus, new genus and Metommatus, new status in the Afrotropical Region." pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
